Acanthicus.label: Acanthicus
Acanthicus.description:
Acanthicus is a genus of suckermouth armored catfishes native to South America.
The name Acanthicus is derived from the Greek, akanthikos meaning thorny, spiny. Fish of this genus are known as Lyre tail plecos. Wikipedia

Acanthurus achilles.label: Acanthurus achilles
Acanthurus achilles.description: Acanthurus achilles is a tropical fish with the common names Achilles Tang and Achilles surgeonfish. It is also a salt water habitat. Wikipedia

Acanthurus.label: Acanthurus
Acanthurus.description: Acanthurus is the type genus of the family Acanthuridae. Approximately half of all members of the family are members of the genus Acanthurus. Wikipedia

Acanthurus albipectoralis.label: Acanthurus albipectoralis
Acanthurus albipectoralis.description: The Whitefin surgeonfish is a marine reef tang in the fish family Acanthuridae. Individuals grow to a maximum length of 33 cm. Wikipedia

Acanthurus auranticavus.label: Acanthurus auranticavus
Acanthurus auranticavus.description: Acanthurus auranticavus, is a tropical fish with the common names Orange-socket surgeonfish and Ring-tail surgeon. It was named by Randall in 1956. Wikipedia

Acanthurus coeruleus.label: Acanthurus coeruleus
Acanthurus coeruleus.description: Acanthurus coeruleus is a surgeonfish found commonly in the Atlantic Ocean. It can grow up to 16 inches long. Wikipedia

Acanthurus dussumieri.label: Acanthurus dussumieri
Acanthurus dussumieri.description: Acanthurus dussumieri is a Tang from the Indo-Pacific. It occasionally makes its way into the aquarium trade. It grows to a size of 54 cm in length. Wikipedia

Acanthurus guttatus.label: Acanthurus guttatus
Acanthurus guttatus.description: The Whitespotted surgeonfish or is a marine reef tang in the fish family Acanthuridae. It is found in shallow waters on reefs in the Indo-Pacific. Wikipedia

Acanthurus japonicus.label: Acanthurus japonicus
Acanthurus japonicus.description: Acanthurus japonicus is a Tang from the Indo-West Pacific. It occasionally makes its way into the aquarium trade. It grows to a size of 21 cm in length. It is also known as Japan Surgeonfish, White-faced Surgeonfish and White-nose Surgeonfish. Wikipedia

Acanthurus lineatus.label: Acanthurus lineatus
Acanthurus lineatus.description: Acanthurus lineatus, the lined surgeonfish, is a member of the family Acanthuridae, the surgeonfishes. Other common names include blue banded surgeonfish, blue-lined surgeonfish, clown surgeonfish, striped surgeonfish, and zebra surgeonfish. Wikipedia

Acanthurus maculiceps.label: Acanthurus maculiceps
Acanthurus maculiceps.description: Acanthurus maculiceps is a Tang from the Indo-West Pacific. It is known commonly as the white-freckled surgeonfish It occasionally makes its way into the aquarium trade. It grows to a size of 40 cm in length. Wikipedia

Acanthurus monroviae.label: Acanthurus monroviae
Acanthurus monroviae.description: Acanthurus monroviae is a tropical fish which is found in the eastern Atlantic ocean. It is commercial in fisheries, and is also used in aquariums. It was first named by Franz Steindachner in 1876, and is known commonly as the Monrovia doctorfish. Wikipedia

Acanthurus nigricans.label: Whitecheek surgeonfish
Acanthurus nigricans.description: The whitecheek surgeonfish, also known as the goldenrim surgeonfish or yellow-spotted surgeonfish, Acanthurus nigricans, is a reef-associated tang found from the central Indo-Pacific area to the eastern Pacific coast, Hawaii included. Wikipedia

Acanthurus nigricauda.label: Acanthurus nigricauda
Acanthurus nigricauda.description: Acanthurus nigricauda is a tropical fish with the common name epaulette surgeonfish. Wikipedia

Acanthurus nigroris.label: Acanthurus nigroris
Acanthurus nigroris.description: Acanthurus nigroris is a Tang from the Indo-Pacific. It occasionally makes its way into the aquarium trade. It grows to a size of 25 cm in length. Wikipedia

Acanthurus olivaceus.label: Acanthurus olivaceus
Acanthurus olivaceus.description: Acanthurus olivaceus, also known as Orange band Surgeonfishor Orange-shoulder Surgeonfish, is a member of the family Acanthuridae, the surgeonfishes. It lives in tropical waters of the Indo-west Pacific. Wikipedia

Acanthurus polyzona.label: Acanthurus polyzona
Acanthurus polyzona.description: Acanthurus polyzona is a tropical fish found in coral reefs situated in the western Indian Ocean. It was first named by Pieter Bleeker in 1868, and is commonly known as the Black-barred surgeonfish or Zebra tang. Wikipedia

Acanthurus pyroferus.label: Acanthurus pyroferus
Acanthurus pyroferus.description: Acanthurus pyroferus is a species of fish in the family Acanthuridae, the unicornfishes and tangs. Its common names include chocolate surgeonfish, mimic surgeonfish, orange-gilled surgeonfish, Pacific mimic surgeon, and yellowspot surgeon. Wikipedia

Acanthurus randalli.label: Acanthurus randalli
Acanthurus randalli.description: Acanthurus randalli is a tropical fish found in the western Atlantic ocean. It was first named by Briggs and Caldwell in 1957, and is commonly known as the Gulf surgeonfish. Wikipedia

Acanthurus reversus.label: Acanthurus reversus
Acanthurus reversus.description: Acanthurus reversus is a tropical fish found in coral reefs in the Marquesas Islands. It was first named by Randall and Earle in 1999. Wikipedia

Acanthurus tennentii.label: Acanthurus tennentii
Acanthurus tennentii.description: The doubleband surgeonfish or lieutenant tang is a marine reef tang in the fish family Acanthuridae. The fish grows to a maximum length of 31 cm. Wikipedia

Acanthurus thompsoni.label: Acanthurus thompsoni
Acanthurus thompsoni.description: Acanthurus thompsoni is a tropical fish found in the Pacific and Indian Oceans. It is commonly known as the Thompson's surgeonfish. It is commercial in aquarium use. Wikipedia

Acanthurus triostegus.label: Acanthurus triostegus
Acanthurus triostegus.description: The manini is a small surgeonfish in family Acanthuridae of order Perciformes. It is about 5 inches long. It is whitish-yellow with zebra-like black stripes on its sides. It is also known as Convict Tang. Wikipedia

Ambassidae.label: Ambassidae
Ambassidae.description: The Asiatic glassfish are a family, Ambassidae, of freshwater and marine fishes in the order Perciformes. The species in the family are native to the waters of Asia and Oceania and the Indian and western Pacific Oceans. Wikipedia

Amberjack.label: Amberjack
Amberjack.description:
Amberjack refers to three species of Atlantic fish of the Carangidae family, which includes the jacks and the pompanos.
Greater amberjacks, Seriola dumerili, are the largest of the jacks. Wikipedia

Amblyopsidae.label: Amblyopsidae
Amblyopsidae.description: The Amblyopsidae are a fish family commonly referred to as cavefish, blindfish, or swampfish. They are small freshwater fish found in the dark environments of swamps, caves, and deep lakes in the eastern half of the United States. Wikipedia

American paddlefish.label: American paddlefish
American paddlefish.description: The American paddlefish, Polyodon spathula, also called the Mississippi paddlefish or spoonbill, is a paddlefish living in slow-flowing waters of the Mississippi River drainage system. Wikipedia

Ammocrypta.label: Ammocrypta
Ammocrypta.description: Sand darters are a genus, Ammocrypta, of perches native to Canada and the continental United States. Wikipedia

Amur pike.label: Amur pike
Amur pike.description: The Amur pike, also known as the blackspotted pike, Esox reichertii, is a pike native to the Amur River system in east Asia, as well as freshwater habitat on the island of Sakhalin. Wikipedia

Anglerfish.label: Anglerfish
Anglerfish.description: Anglerfishes are members of the teleost order Lophiiformes. They are bony fishes named for their characteristic mode of predation, in which a fleshy growth from the fish's head acts as a lure. Wikipedia

Anthiinae.label: Anthiinae
Anthiinae.description: Anthias are members of the family Serranidae and make up the subfamily Anthiinae. Anthias make up a sizeable portion of the population of pink, orange and yellow reef fishes seen swarming in most coral reef photography and film. Wikipedia

Aphanotorulus.label: Aphanotorulus
Aphanotorulus.description: Aphanotorulus is a genus of armored catfishes native to South America. Wikipedia

Archerfish.label: Archerfish
Archerfish.description: The archerfish are a family of fish known for their habit of preying on land-based insects and other small animals by shooting them down with water droplets from their specialized mouths. Wikipedia

Argentina elongata.label: Argentina elongata
Argentina elongata.description: Argentina elongata is a herring smelt found around southern Australia, and New Zealand, at depths of between 69 and 600 m. Its length is up to 25.0 centimetres. It is a species of minor importance to local commercial fisheries. Wikipedia

Argyripnus.label: Argyripnus
Argyripnus.description: Argyripnus is an oceanic ray-finned fish genus which belongs in the family Sternoptychidae. They are commonly known as bristle-mouth fishes, but that may also refer to the related bristlemouth family. Wikipedia

Armored searobin.label: Armored searobin
Armored searobin.description: The armored searobins, or armored gurnards are a family, Peristediidae, of scorpaeniform fishes. They are found in deep tropical waters around the world. Wikipedia

Asian arowana.label: Asian arowana
Asian arowana.description: The Asian arowana comprises several phenotypic varieties of freshwater fish distributed geographically across Southeast Asia. Wikipedia

Astrapogon.label: Astrapogon
Astrapogon.description: Astrapogon is a genus of cardinalfishes native to the western Atlantic Ocean. Wikipedia

Atherinomorus.label: Atherinomorus
Atherinomorus.description: Atherinomorus is a genus of silversides in the family, Atherinidae. Wikipedia

Atlantic flyingfish.label: Atlantic flyingfish
Atlantic flyingfish.description: The Atlantic flyingfish is a flying fish in the family Exocoetidae. It was first described by the French zoologist, Achille Valenciennes in a 22-volume work entitled Histoire naturelle des poissons, ... Wikipedia

Atlantic lizardfish.label: Atlantic lizardfish
Atlantic lizardfish.description: The Atlantic lizardfish, is a species of lizardfish that primarily lives in the Eastern Atlantic. Wikipedia

Atlantic stargazer.label: Atlantic stargazer
Atlantic stargazer.description: Atlantic stargazer is a marine, subtropical fish of family Uranoscopidae. Its body is suited for living on the sea floor, and is one of few fish capable of bioelectrogenesis, or the ability to generate an electric charge. Wikipedia

Atlantic menhaden.label: Atlantic menhaden
Atlantic menhaden.description: The Atlantic menhaden is a silvery, highly compressed fish in the herring family, Clupeidae. A filter feeder, it lives on plankton caught in midwater. Wikipedia

Atlantic threadfin.label: Atlantic threadfin
Atlantic threadfin.description: The Atlantic threadfin, Polydactylus octonemus, is a threadfin native to subtropical and temperate waters of the western Atlantic Ocean and the Gulf of Mexico. It grows up to 23 cm in length. Wikipedia

Banded archerfish.label: Banded archerfish
Banded archerfish.description: The banded archerfish is a brackish water perciform fish of the archerfish genus Toxotes. It is silvery in colour and has a dorsal fin towards the posterior end. It has distinctive, semi-triangular markings along its sides. Wikipedia

Banded knifefish.label: Banded knifefish
Banded knifefish.description:
The banded knifefish is a knifefish native to South America.
The banded knifefish is gray in color with a band of large black spots outlined with yellow on either side. It can reach up to 60 cm in length. Wikipedia

Barcoo grunter.label: Scortum barcoo
Barcoo grunter.description: Scortum barcoo is a species of fish in the family Terapontidae known by the common names Barcoo grunter. It is endemic to Australia, where it can be found in certain major rivers, including the Barcoo River. It is reared in hatcheries. Wikipedia

Barramundi.label: Barramundi
Barramundi.description: The barramundi' or Asian seabass is a species of catadromous fish in family Latidae of order Perciformes. Wikipedia

Barreleye.label: Barreleye
Barreleye.description: Barreleyes, also known as spook fish, are small deep-sea argentiniform fish comprising the family Opisthoproctidae found in tropical-to-temperate waters of the Atlantic, Pacific, and Indian Oceans. Wikipedia

Bastard trumpeter.label: Bastard trumpeter
Bastard trumpeter.description: Latridopsis forsteri, the bastard trumpeter or copper moki, is a species of trumpeter native to the eastern Indian Ocean and southwestern Pacific Ocean around Australia and New Zealand. Wikipedia

Bedotia madagascariensis.label: Bedotia madagascariensis
Bedotia madagascariensis.description: The zona is a species of fish in the Bedotiidae family. It is endemic to Madagascar. Its natural habitats are rivers and freshwater lakes. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Bembridae.label: Bembridae
Bembridae.description: The deep-water flatheads are a family, the Bembridae, of bottom-dwelling fish. They are thought to be more primitive than their close relatives, the true flatheads. Wikipedia

Benthochromis.label: Benthochromis
Benthochromis.description: Benthochromis is a small genus of cichlid fish endemic to Lake Tanganyika in east Africa. Wikipedia

Berycidae.label: Berycidae
Berycidae.description: The Berycidae are a small family of deep-sea fishes, related to the squirrelfishes. The family includes the alfonsinos and the nannygais. Wikipedia

Big-eyed cardinalfish.label: Big-eyed cardinalfish
Big-eyed cardinalfish.description: The big-eyed cardinalfish or bigeye cardinalfish, Epigonus lenimen, is a species of deepwater cardinalfish found in the southern Indian Ocean and southwestern Pacific Ocean from south of Madagascar to New Zealand. Wikipedia

Black butterflyfish.label: Black butterflyfish
Black butterflyfish.description: The Black Butterflyfish is a species of butterflyfish native to the Pacific Ocean where it can be found inhabiting reefs at depths of from 2 to 20 metres extending from Australia to Pitcairn Island. Wikipedia

Black cod.label: Black cod
Black cod.description: The black cod or smallscaled cod, Notothenia microlepidota, is a species of cod icefish native to the Pacific waters around New Zealand and Macquarie Island. This species can reach a length of 70 centimetres TL. Wikipedia

Black ghost knifefish.label: Black ghost knifefish
Black ghost knifefish.description: The black ghost knifefish, Apteronotus albifrons, is a tropical fish belonging to the ghost knifefish family. They originate in South America in the Amazon Basin in Peru and from Venezuela through Paraguay in the Paran√° River. Wikipedia

Blackspotted stickleback.label: Blackspotted stickleback
Blackspotted stickleback.description: Blackspotted stickleback is a fish species, found in the western Atlantic from the coasts of Newfoundland to Massachusetts. Brackishwater / marine benthic fish, up to 7.5 cm length. Wikipedia

Blotched fantail ray.label: Round ribbontail ray
Blotched fantail ray.description: The round ribbontail ray is a species of stingray in the family Dasyatidae, found throughout the nearshore waters of the tropical Indo-Pacific, as well as off islands in the eastern Pacific. Wikipedia

Blue grenadier.label: Blue grenadier
Blue grenadier.description: The blue grenadier, hoki, blue hake, New Zealand whiptail, whiptail or whiptail hake, Macruronus novaezelandiae, is a merluccid hake of the family Merlucciidae found around southern Australia and New Zealand at depths of between 10 and 1,000 m. Wikipedia

Blue moki.label: Blue moki
Blue moki.description: Latridopsis ciliaris, the Blue moki, is a species of trumpeter native to the southwestern Pacific Ocean around New Zealand and occasionally off southeastern Australia at depths of 10 metres and greater. Wikipedia

Blue ring angelfish.label: Blue ring angelfish
Blue ring angelfish.description: The bluering angelfish is an angelfish of the family Pomacanthidae, found in the Indo-West Pacific oceans from East Africa, throughout Indonesia and New Guinea to New Caledonia, north to southern Japan. Wikipedia

Blue knifefish.label: Blue knifefish
Blue knifefish.description: The blue knifefish, Labracoglossa nitida, is a species of sea chub native to the Pacific Ocean waters off eastern Australia over to New Zealand, where it occurs at depths reaching from the surface to 20 m in inshore waters over reefs. Wikipedia

Boreogadus saida.label: Boreogadus saida
Boreogadus saida.description: Boreogadus saida, known as the polar cod or as the Arctic cod, is a fish of the cod family Gadidae, related to the true cod. Wikipedia

Bonefishes.label: Bonefishes
Bonefishes.description: The bonefishes are a family of ray-finned fish that are popular as game fish in Florida, select locations in the South Pacific, and the Bahamas and elsewhere. The family is small, with 12 species in two genera. Wikipedia

Bony bream.label: Bony bream
Bony bream.description: Bony bream Nematalosa erebi are a widespread and common, small to medium sized Australian freshwater fish often found in large shoals throughout much of northern and central Australia, and the Murray-Darling basin. Wikipedia

Brachypterois serrulata.label: Brachypterois serrulata
Brachypterois serrulata.description: Brachypterois serrulata, the Sawtooth Scorpionfish is a species of scorpionfish native to the northwestern Pacific Ocean. Wikipedia

Callionymoidei.label: Callionymoidei
Callionymoidei.description: Callionymoidei is a suborder of the Perciformes, the largest order of fish. The suborder includes the Dragonets. Wikipedia

Cape conger.label: Cape conger
Cape conger.description: The cape conger, Conger wilsoni, is a conger of the family Congridae, found around southern Australia and the east coast of the North Island of New Zealand. Length is up to 1 m. Wikipedia

Centropyge.label: Centropyge
Centropyge.description: Centropyge is a genus of marine angelfishes. The genus is the largest within the Pomacanthid family, comprising over 30 described species. Wikipedia

Caproidae.label: Caproidae
Caproidae.description: Boarfishes are a small family, Caproidae, of marine fishes comprising two genera and 12 species. They were formerly placed in the order Zeiformes with the dories, but are now placed with the Perciformes ... Wikipedia

Careproctus.label: Careproctus
Careproctus.description: Careproctus is a genus of snailfishes found in benthic and benthopelagic habitats in the Atlantic and Pacific Oceans. They range from shallow coastal waters to depths below 7000 m. Wikipedia

Characodon.label: Characodon
Characodon.description: Characodon is a genus of splitfins endemic to Mexico. Wikipedia

Cephalaspis.label: Cephalaspis
Cephalaspis.description: Cephalaspis was a genus in the class Osteostraci of Palaeozoic armoured jawless fishes, or ostracoderms. It was a medium sized detritivorous fish that lived in freshwater streams and estuaries of the early Devonian. Wikipedia

Chinese sturgeon.label: Chinese sturgeon
Chinese sturgeon.description: The Chinese sturgeon is critically endangered member of the family Acipenseridae in the order Acipenseriformes. Wikipedia

Chocolate gourami.label: Chocolate gourami
Chocolate gourami.description: The chocolate gourami, Sphaerichthys osphromenoides, is a small species of gourami. These fish originate from the Malay Peninsula, Sumatra and Borneo. Wikipedia

Cirrhitichthys.label: Cirrhitichthys
Cirrhitichthys.description: Cirrhitichthys is a genus of hawkfishes found on tropical reefs in the Indian and western Pacific oceans. Wikipedia

Cirrhitichthys aureus.label: Yellow hawkfish
Cirrhitichthys aureus.description: The yellow hawkfish, Cirrhitichthys aureus, is a species of hawkfish native to tropical reefs of the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean. This species can reach a length of 14 cm in total length. Wikipedia

Cladistia.label: Cladistia
Cladistia.description: Cladistia is a clade of bony fishes that currently consists of few anguilliform remnants of an ancient diversity. Their major synapomorphies are a dorsal fin with independent rays, and a posteriorly elongated parasphenoid. Wikipedia

Clown loach.label: Clown loach
Clown loach.description: The clown loach, Chromobotia macracanthus, is a tropical freshwater fish belonging to the botiid loach family. It is the sole member of the Chromobotia genus. It originates in inland waters in Indonesia on the islands of Sumatra and Borneo. Wikipedia

Clupeoides.label: Clupeoides
Clupeoides.description: Clupeoides is a genus of sprats that occur in rivers in Southeast Asia. There are currently four recognized species in the genus. Wikipedia

Clupeonella.label: Clupeonella
Clupeonella.description: Clupeonella is a genus of fish in the Clupeidae family. Widespread in the fresh and brackish waters of the Black and Caspian Sea drainages. Wikipedia

Common dab.label: Common dab
Common dab.description: The common dab is an edible flatfish of the family Pleuronectidae. It is a demersal fish native to shallow seas around Northern Europe, in particular the North Sea, where it lives on sandy bottoms down to depths of about 100 metres. Wikipedia

Common ling.label: Common ling
Common ling.description: The common ling or simply the ling, Molva molva, is a large member of a family of cod-like fishes. An ocean fish whose habitat is in the Atlantic region and can be found around Iceland, Faroe Islands, ... Wikipedia
